      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW IMPERIAL (4) ran good time (29.74) when second last start over 515m at this track, the second placing in a row. This looks easier and expected to bounce back. PAW HARRY (2) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by a neck at The Meadows in a handy 30.53 beating Miss Sooky. Has a low draw and in form and has the ability. Has performed well from this box with a win and eight minor placings to his name from 14 starts. Should be in this for a long way. BIG DUKE (1) turned in a plain performance last time when seventh at this track over 515m behind Lush Hour (30.56) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Great chance to atone. ESCAPING BINDI (5) generally performs well here at this distance.",
